###############################################################################
# infra/.github/CODEOWNERS
#
# GitHub CODEOWNERS file. Defines who must approve a PR before it
# can merge. The pattern is "later match wins" -- the most specific
# rule at the bottom of the file overrides the more general ones
# above it.
#
# Reviewer placeholders: the @niahealth-* team handles are
# placeholders the team will create in the GitHub UI:
#   - @niahealth-security  -- security review (IAM, KMS, WAF, OIDC)
#   - @niahealth-eng       -- engineering review (workflows, modules)
#   - @niahealth-compliance-- compliance review (controls, policies)
# The user's personal handle @AnandSundar is the default owner for
# everything; the team handles layer specific responsibilities on
# top of that.
#
# The `apply.yml` workflow requires 2 reviewers (security + eng).
# This is the last-line defense against a malicious or accidental
# change to the production-apply path.
###############################################################################

# Default: every change in the repo requires a review from the
# project owner. Team handles add layered review on top of this.
*                                                       @AnandSundar

# Identity and observability modules touch IAM roles, CloudTrail,
# and GuardDuty/Config. These are the highest-blast-radius
# resources; require an explicit security review.
infra/modules/identity/                                  @niahealth-security
infra/modules/observability/                             @niahealth-security

# Apply workflow: changes here can drive a production apply.
# Require BOTH security and engineering review -- two pairs of
# eyes on the single most powerful file in the repo.
infra/.github/workflows/apply.yml                        @niahealth-security @niahealth-eng

# Plan workflow: one engineering reviewer is sufficient.
infra/.github/workflows/plan.yml                         @niahealth-eng

# Policy changes (Checkov, OPA, tflint) need a compliance review
# because they encode the control matrix.
infra/policies/                                          @niahealth-compliance
